{
  "texts": [
    "Within each set, we grouped the vectors into their respective movement direction (4 directions defined by each quadrant in the unit circle) for each hand.",
    "Grouping the bimanual trials for right hand movement direction ignored left hand movement direction and vice versa.",
    "This resulted in 4 total sets of firing rate vectors grouped by their respective hand's movement direction (unimanual right directions, unimanual left directions, bimanual right directions, and bimanual left directions) and a separate 1-way ANOVA was performed within each set.",
    "If the p-value was less than 0.00001, the electrode was considered to be strongly tuned to that movement context (unimanual or bimanual).",
    "To assess the tuning strength of each strongly tuned electrode, we computed FVAF (fraction of variance accounted for) scores 27, 63."
  ]
}